Tool Card: get_weather_data

General Info

    Name: get_weather_data
    Title: Weather Data Retriever
    Version: 1.0.0
    Author: Example Dev Team
    Description: Retrieves current weather data for a given location.

Intended Use

    For conversational agents needing lightweight, real-time weather.
    Read-only access; no side effects.

Out-of-Scope / Limitations

    Only supports city names and ZIP codes.
    Limited to current weather; no forecast.
    Requires external API key.

Input Schema

{

  "type": "object",

  "properties": {

    "location": { "type": "string", "description": "City or ZIP" },

    "units": { "type": "string", "enum": ["metric","imperial"], "default": "metric" }

  },

  "required": ["location"]

}

Output Schema

{

  "type": "object",

  "properties": {

    "temperature": { "type": "number", "description": "°C or °F" },

    "conditions": { "type": "string" },

    "humidity": { "type": "number" }

  },

  "required": ["temperature","conditions","humidity"]

}

Example

    Input:
    { "location": "Baltimore", "units": "imperial" }
    Output:
    {
      "temperature": 72.5,
      "conditions": "Partly Cloudy",
      "humidity": 65
    }

Safety & Reliability

    Validates inputs against schema.
    Returns error if location cannot be resolved.
    No PII collected; logs disabled.